Title: 2013 Coachmen Leprechaun M260QB
text: We're selling to upgrade to larger unit. Got this RV last summer but find ourselves cramped with 4 of us plus our 2 dogs. We ran it a couple trips to Kenai and Seward. We're several thousand below NADA. M260QB,  28 foot model, LX package. Will sleep 6-8 depending on folks' size. Couch is jackknife model plus the overhead queen bed and the dinette makes a bed. Capacities-55 gallons fuel, 29 black tank, 25 grey. 16 gallons propane. This RV is set on a Chevy chassis with a 6.0 liter gasoline engine and has loads of power if you're in a hurry to get to your fishing spots. RV includes a TV/monitor and 12 volt plug ins plus 110 off the gen set, Onan 4K model.  Has a convection microwave oven, a 3 burner range top, and lots of cabinet space. The slide out includes the couch and kitchen stove giving plenty cook prep space not to mention leg room. Awning over slide. Glass shower enclosure with light and skylight. Bathroom actually has room enough to do the deed in comfort. Kitchen sink faucet with pull out sprayer. The entry door has two steps up into the RV but no steps outside to deal with. Full electric awning which is just awesome. Don't think I'll ever have a manual one again. Has backup camera plus side turning blind spot cameras to let you know if some idiot is beside you while you're trying to turn. All tires brand new in late July. New air filter. Has huge rear storage space that will hold kids' bikes no problem plus lots more. Has a huge led light bar but one half is not working so sorry about that. The side that works could spot a moose from here to Yellowstone though! Please text or call for details and showing. Not yet winterized so you can take it camping this weekend!

Title: Schwinn varsity
